Subject: Re: [VB] Re: Steering column switches

like Matt said, the switch is for only the rear dome light.    That way you 
can turn the light off/on from the drivers seat if it is on at the switch 
back there.   For some reason, my 61 is wired so that the switch does the 
front dome light as well and I like it like that.

The switch colour matches the knob colour, so black, 'grey' or the off white, 
depending on year and model.  Screw or push on terminals.  there  are so many 
to choose from!

there is a very similar switch in my 69 bug for the rear window defogger.  
Might be the same thing.


